<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate Disclosure — MailPilot"
  description="How MailPilot makes money and how that affects our recommendations."
>
  <h1>Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
  <p class="meta">Last updated: 2026-07-02</p>

  <p>MailPilot is an independent review site. We earn revenue through affiliate links — when you click a link on this site and sign up for a tool we recommend, we may receive a commission from that vendor. <strong>This costs you nothing extra.</strong></p>

  <h2>How this affects our reviews</h2>
  <p>It doesn't. We have three rules we don't break:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>We never accept payment for a review.</strong> If a vendor offers to pay us to write a positive review, we say no.</li>
    <li><strong>We only recommend tools we'd use ourselves.</strong> If we wouldn't run our own business on a tool, we won't recommend it to you.</li>
    <li><strong>Cons go in the review, not in a footnote.</strong> If a tool has a real downside, we say so — even if it costs us the commission.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Affiliate programs we participate in</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Amazon Associates</li>
    <li>ShareASale (Brevo, ConvertKit, ActiveCampaign, and others)</li>
    <li>PartnerStack</li>
    <li>Impact</li>
    <li>Individual vendor programs (MailerLite, Mailchimp, Kit, etc.)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>No sponsored content</h2>
  <p>If a vendor sponsors a post, we label it clearly at the top. Unsponsored reviews never mention sponsors.</p>
</BaseLayout>